        <div class="panel-inner">
            <h4>LL05 Frequenty Asked Questions</h4>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL05-046/">LL05-046 "Chika Takami"</a></h5>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#stand_by">What is the "On Stand-By" state?</a>
            </div>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#skill_order_same_skill">Does the order of Actions in a Skill matter?</a>
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="046">
                There are three conditions and effects each, can I use multiple effects of
                the <%- skillFormat("[Entry]") %> Skill if the respective conditions are met?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                Yes. For example, if you have no cards in your Hand and no Song cards used for Lives when this card
                is <%- skillFormat("⟪ENTER⟫ed, you may both draw three cards and perform a ⟪LIVE⟫") %> with
                this card.
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL05-047/">LL05-047 "Riko Sakurauchi"</a></h5>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#skill_order_multiple_skills">What if a Member card has two or more
                    Skills?</a>
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="047_other">
                On the turn after this card
                was <%- skillFormat("⟪ENTER⟫ed, another <a href=\"/card/LL05-047/\">LL05-047 \"Riko Sakurauchi\"</a> was ⟪ENTER⟫ed. Can this card join a ⟪LIVE⟫") %>
                in my next turn?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                Yes.
                The <%- skillFormat("[Entry] Skills are handled seperately for each card, so the first card can join a ⟪LIVE⟫") %>
                . However, the second <span class="redtext">"Riko"</span> will not be able to join yet in that turn.
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="047_live">
                I used this
                card's <%- skillFormat("[RUSH] to ⟪ENTER⟫ another Member with [LIVE]. Can I perform a ⟪LIVE⟫?") %>
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                Yes. This card cannot join
                the <%- skillFormat("⟪LIVE⟫ due to the Skill, but you can still perform ⟪LIVE⟫s using other Members' [LIVE].") %>
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL05-048/">LL05-048 "Kanan Matsuura"</a></h5>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#skill_order_multiple_skills">What if a Member card has two or more
                    Skills?</a>
            </div>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#stand_by">What is the "On Stand-By" state?</a>
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="048">
                I <%- skillFormat("⟪ENTER⟫ed this card using the [RUSH] from the [RUSH]/[LIVE] of <a href=\"/card/LL04-053/\">LL04-053 \"Mari Ohara\"</a>. In this case, can I perform a ⟪LIVE⟫") %>
                with those two cards?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                Yes. The <span class="redtext">"Mari"</span> card has
                a <%- skillFormat("[LIVE] icon, so you can use this card's Skill to perform a ⟪LIVE⟫") %>.
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL05-049/">LL05-049 "Dia Kurosawa"</a></h5>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#skill_order_multiple_skills">What if a Member card has two or more
                    Skills?</a>
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="049_both">
                If both Skill's requirements are met, does this card get both Pieces?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                Yes. In that case, you will get two Pieces, one from each Skill.
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="049_name">
                If this card joins
                a <%- skillFormat("⟪LIVE⟫ with <a href=\"/card/LL04-057/\">LL04-057 \"Aqours☆HEROES\"</a> as the Song card, does it get +[ALL]") %>
                from the second Skill?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                No. The Song title is not part of the Skill text, so the requirement for the second Skill is not met.
            </div>

